Conductor Leonard Bernstein has canceled several

Bernstein, 71, has suffered from severe influenza, pleurisy, and pneumonia since the beginning of the year, Cahill said in a statement released by Harry Kraut, Bernstein's manager.
Dr. Angelo Aquista, an associate of Cahill, flew to Japan to accompany the conductor back to New York, it said.
Kraut did not provide the time or date of Bernstein's departure.
Bernstein inaugurated the festival last month.
Kraut's statement said it was not known whether Bernstein would be able to conduct next month at the Tanglewood festival or during the Tanglewood Music Center Orchestra Tour in Europe later this summer.
